1
00:00:01,835 --> 00:00:03,169
[Harold] <i>My memories are back, sir.</i>

2
00:00:03,753 --> 00:00:05,171
[in English] Welcome back, Rustia.

3
00:00:05,255 --> 00:00:06,548
[Marcus] <i>When you're back at the NLEA,</i>

4
00:00:06,631 --> 00:00:08,174
<i>keep quiet about what you know.</i>

5
00:00:08,758 --> 00:00:10,427
<i>Especially around Felix.</i>

6
00:00:10,510 --> 00:00:11,720
About Cuchy…

7
00:00:11,803 --> 00:00:13,304
[Felix] <i>I adopted her. I took care of her.</i>

8
00:00:13,388 --> 00:00:15,181
<i>But she disappeared all of a sudden.</i>

9
00:00:15,265 --> 00:00:16,433
Who is this "Cuchy"?

10
00:00:16,516 --> 00:00:19,144
You really do have a lot
of things you don't remember.

11
00:00:19,227 --> 00:00:20,645
[in English] Good to see you, Felix.

12
00:00:20,729 --> 00:00:22,689
[Harold] <i>If you really are</i>
<i>the traitor among us,</i>

13
00:00:23,273 --> 00:00:25,734
<i>I'll make sure you pay.</i>

14
00:00:25,817 --> 00:00:28,695
[Villanueva, in English]
<i>You are hereby fired</i>

15
00:00:28,778 --> 00:00:31,698
<i>as the director of the Special</i>
<i>Investigations Division!</i>

16
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:32,991
Effective immediately,

17
00:00:33,074 --> 00:00:34,576
Task Force Alpha

18
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:36,578
is hereby dissolved!

19
00:00:36,661 --> 00:00:38,872
[suspenseful music playing]

20
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:41,082
[Marcus] <i>You need to watch your back</i>
<i>and find somewhere to hide.</i>

21
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:42,834
<i>You'll definitely be targeted.</i>

22
00:00:42,917 --> 00:00:45,295
They could strike back
and use you against us.

23
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:48,131
[Norhana] <i>As long as you're in</i>
<i>our community, you're safe.</i>

24
00:00:48,214 --> 00:00:49,549
[Marcus] <i>When this is all over,</i>

25
00:00:49,632 --> 00:00:51,342
<i>we'll have so much to catch up on</i>

26
00:00:51,426 --> 00:00:53,136
<i>and discover about each other.</i>

27
00:00:53,219 --> 00:00:57,724
But for now, we need
to take down General Carillo.

28
00:00:57,807 --> 00:00:59,017
The sooner, the better.

29
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,143
I need your help.

30
00:01:00,226 --> 00:01:02,896
[Edrick] <i>Datu Rahman</i>
<i>gave an envelope to Ms. MMK.</i>

31
00:01:02,979 --> 00:01:05,315
- What's on it?
- Substantial evidence, sir,

32
00:01:05,398 --> 00:01:06,900
against General Carillo.

33
00:01:06,983 --> 00:01:08,777
[in English] The answers
we are searching for

34
00:01:08,860 --> 00:01:10,153
- are just here.
- [gunshots blasting]

35
00:01:10,236 --> 00:01:11,654
[screaming]

36
00:01:11,738 --> 00:01:15,283
[Maya Mae] And because these documents
will reveal everything.

37
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:17,744
[Maya Mae] <i>And when we did</i>
<i>our preliminary investigation,</i>

38
00:01:17,827 --> 00:01:21,164
<i>we saw a lot of familiar names</i>
<i>in this document.</i>

39
00:01:21,247 --> 00:01:22,874
[Maya Mae] But the most
frequent one of all

40
00:01:22,957 --> 00:01:27,712
was the name of retired
police general Manuel Carillo.

41
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:30,423
[Manuel] <i>I won't let</i>
<i>that damned Marcus and Jalil</i>

42
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:33,718
<i>bring me down!</i>

43
00:01:33,802 --> 00:01:36,679
[reporter] <i>Retired police general</i>
<i>Manuel Carillo was arrested.</i>

44
00:01:36,763 --> 00:01:40,225
<i>This was after Maya Mae Kalaw</i>
<i>made an exposé</i>

45
00:01:40,308 --> 00:01:43,603
<i>linking General Carillo</i>
<i>to a gun-smuggling syndicate</i>

46
00:01:43,686 --> 00:01:46,105
<i>and an alleged plot to overthrow</i>
<i>the government.</i>

47
00:01:46,898 --> 00:01:51,194
[mysterious theme music playing]

48
00:02:02,914 --> 00:02:06,334
[morose music playing]

49
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:22,142
Sorry… I'm sorry, General.

50
00:02:22,225 --> 00:02:25,854
[handcuffs click open]

51
00:02:36,614 --> 00:02:39,534
[breathes sharply and loudly]

52
00:02:39,617 --> 00:02:40,618
I'm exhausted.

53
00:02:45,373 --> 00:02:46,958
At last,

54
00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:50,461
the people behind all this chaos
have finally been locked up.

55
00:02:50,545 --> 00:02:52,255
I know, right?

56
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:54,549
Can you believe General Carillo
was behind all of it?

57
00:02:54,632 --> 00:02:57,510
He seemed nice, but he was evil all along.

58
00:02:57,594 --> 00:03:01,890
You really can't judge
a person's true character

59
00:03:01,973 --> 00:03:03,516
just by how they look.

60
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:04,767
[Norhana] That's true.

61
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:07,979
But I'm even happier because…

62
00:03:08,062 --> 00:03:13,651
I finally get to see my children again
and be with them.

63
00:03:13,735 --> 00:03:15,486
[knocking on door]

64
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:25,163
[in Arabic] Praise be to God!

65
00:03:25,246 --> 00:03:26,372
- Ma…
- Marcus.

66
00:03:27,498 --> 00:03:29,000
Auntie.

67
00:03:30,126 --> 00:03:31,336
[softly] How are you?

68
00:03:38,551 --> 00:03:39,886
Gabriel…

69
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:44,766
[emotional music playing]

70
00:03:44,849 --> 00:03:45,808
Gabriel…

71
00:03:46,476 --> 00:03:47,644
[sniffles]

72
00:03:47,727 --> 00:03:49,312
- Mama.
- [sobs]

73
00:03:49,395 --> 00:03:50,980
My son!

74
00:03:52,273 --> 00:03:54,442
[crying]

75
00:03:54,525 --> 00:03:55,610
- Mama…
- [crying, sobbing]

76
00:04:00,865 --> 00:04:02,659
[sniffles, sobbing]

77
00:04:03,451 --> 00:04:06,120
- [smooches]
- [crying]

78
00:04:06,204 --> 00:04:08,081
[in Arabic] Praise be to God!

79
00:04:08,164 --> 00:04:09,499
[indistinct]

80
00:04:14,879 --> 00:04:16,005
Gabriel.

81
00:04:18,675 --> 00:04:19,926
Marcus…

82
00:04:22,595 --> 00:04:25,139
I'm so glad you're both safe, my children.

83
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:31,396
General Carillo's accomplices
are still in hiding,

84
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:34,023
but we'll find them.

85
00:04:36,859 --> 00:04:38,569
We're still not completely safe, Ma.

86
00:04:39,737 --> 00:04:42,657
Not until everything
has truly been resolved.

87
00:04:44,909 --> 00:04:48,037
You two still need
to be careful, my children.

88
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:50,290
Even though Carillo is in prison,

89
00:04:50,873 --> 00:04:53,960
he's still dangerous because his influence
reaches far and wide.

90
00:05:06,764 --> 00:05:08,808
- Sir!
- Oh!

91
00:05:09,434 --> 00:05:11,602
Azuelo, what do you need?

92
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:15,982
Sir, now that General Carillo
has been arrested,

93
00:05:16,858 --> 00:05:21,904
and it's been proven
that I had nothing to do

94
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:25,533
with the gun smuggling
and the destabilization plot

95
00:05:25,616 --> 00:05:26,784
against the government,

96
00:05:26,868 --> 00:05:29,912
- I'm hoping you could reconsider--
- [Villanueva] Do you want to know

97
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:34,334
if you'll be reinstated as SID Director?

98
00:05:34,917 --> 00:05:36,878
- [in English] Yes, sir.
- [Villanueva] Azuelo.

99
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:41,424
We have standard procedures
that need to be followed.

100
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:44,552
We can't rush the process.

101
00:05:48,389 --> 00:05:49,807
[in English] I understand, sir.

102
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:52,602
[in English] How about…

103
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:56,355
Agent Marcus Reyes
and Jalil Abubakar, sir?

104
00:05:58,024 --> 00:06:00,526
I've already removed them
from the most wanted list.

105
00:06:01,611 --> 00:06:06,240
They're no longer under
the neutralize-on-sight order.

106
00:06:06,324 --> 00:06:09,160
But they still have
a lot of charges to face.

107
00:06:09,243 --> 00:06:11,537
And they still have
a lot of explaining to do.

108
00:06:12,288 --> 00:06:13,539
[in English] That would be all, sir.

109
00:06:14,165 --> 00:06:16,292
- [in English] Sir!
- [in English] Carry on.

110
00:06:16,375 --> 00:06:20,213
[tense music playing]

111
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:31,641
[door clicks shut]

112
00:06:31,724 --> 00:06:33,851
[Sean] That's all
General Villanueva said, sir?

113
00:06:34,852 --> 00:06:36,395
He removed you
from your position fast enough.

114
00:06:36,479 --> 00:06:38,106
[Eve] Exactly.

115
00:06:38,189 --> 00:06:39,941
But now he's saying…

116
00:06:40,817 --> 00:06:42,735
there's a process that can't be rushed?

117
00:06:42,819 --> 00:06:44,779
Sir! My goodness.

118
00:06:44,862 --> 00:06:47,323
Sir, they're intentionally
doing it to cause delay.

119
00:06:47,406 --> 00:06:50,284
[stirring music playing]

120
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:54,080
You're right. I've also noticed that
he seems to be acting differently now.

121
00:06:55,373 --> 00:06:57,166
It's as if he's waiting for something.

122
00:06:58,334 --> 00:06:59,877
What do you mean, sir?

123
00:07:01,546 --> 00:07:03,089
I'm not yet sure.

124
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:07,260
But he's really acting
suspiciously right now.

125
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:11,889
[footsteps approaching]

126
00:07:15,226 --> 00:07:18,813
[Manuel inhales and exhales deeply]

127
00:07:19,856 --> 00:07:21,357
[in English] Madam President.

128
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:24,777
How may I help you?

129
00:07:25,278 --> 00:07:30,616
[in English] But as you can see,
I'm… currently indisposed.

130
00:07:32,076 --> 00:07:33,369
[in English] How dare you?

131
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:38,458
[in English] I trusted you,
but you played me for a fool!

132
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:41,752
You even killed Ahmad.

133
00:07:42,336 --> 00:07:46,090
The only person I trusted a lot.

134
00:07:46,674 --> 00:07:48,801
I hope you know, General Carillo,

135
00:07:48,885 --> 00:07:51,637
that you didn't just betray me.

136
00:07:52,346 --> 00:07:54,056
You betrayed the whole country!

137
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:56,642
[tense music playing]

138
00:07:56,726 --> 00:07:59,437
I never denied it.

139
00:08:00,271 --> 00:08:01,564
[chuckles, inhales]

140
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:04,901
[Manuel, in English]
Look at yourself. You're so weak.

141
00:08:05,902 --> 00:08:07,403
You're too weak.

142
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:10,990
You have to trust me.

143
00:08:11,574 --> 00:08:13,701
You know nothing.

144
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:16,579
I was just playing you.

145
00:08:18,247 --> 00:08:19,373
I'm…

146
00:08:20,374 --> 00:08:21,542
weak?

147
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:25,171
You're the one in jail.

148
00:08:26,088 --> 00:08:28,591
Remember this, General Carillo.

149
00:08:29,175 --> 00:08:33,846
I will do everything in my power
as president of the republic

150
00:08:33,930 --> 00:08:38,184
to make sure that you
and your collaborators

151
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:40,019
will pay for all of your sins!

152
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:55,660
[pensive music playing]

153
00:08:58,871 --> 00:09:00,289
[Jalil sighs]

154
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:03,376
What's your plan now?

155
00:09:05,753 --> 00:09:07,255
I'll return to the SID.

156
00:09:08,506 --> 00:09:10,967
I'll make sure to bring back
the Task Force Alpha.

157
00:09:12,009 --> 00:09:13,261
And you?

158
00:09:15,972 --> 00:09:18,432
I'll bring back my father's corpse
to the island.

159
00:09:20,351 --> 00:09:22,353
That's what I promised him and Jamilah.

160
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:24,564
And after that?

161
00:09:25,481 --> 00:09:26,941
What will you do then?

162
00:09:27,024 --> 00:09:28,276
I don't know.

163
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:32,446
Will you stay in your island or…

164
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:35,116
will you stay here in Manila?

165
00:09:35,199 --> 00:09:40,788
Maybe… It might be better
if you stay here in Manila for now.

166
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:43,916
You know.

167
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:47,086
Mom will miss you if you leave right away.

168
00:09:52,049 --> 00:09:54,176
I'm a member of CDSU-Mindanao.

169
00:09:55,886 --> 00:09:58,639
- My life is really there.
- You know, that's another thing.

170
00:10:00,141 --> 00:10:02,226
Why don't you just continue
being a police officer here?

171
00:10:03,227 --> 00:10:05,062
Is that even possible
after everything that happened?

172
00:10:05,688 --> 00:10:06,897
We don't know.

173
00:10:08,024 --> 00:10:09,358
It'll be a shame.

174
00:10:10,651 --> 00:10:11,902
You're great.

175
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:15,865
I know you really want
to be a police officer.

176
00:10:16,907 --> 00:10:19,660
Not everything we want will happen.

177
00:10:22,538 --> 00:10:24,874
Right now, I'm happy to…

178
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:27,418
meet you and Mom.

179
00:10:28,878 --> 00:10:32,006
The most important thing for me now is,

180
00:10:32,089 --> 00:10:35,926
how do we find
Carillo's remaining accomplices?

181
00:10:36,010 --> 00:10:38,137
[stirring music playing]

182
00:10:38,721 --> 00:10:40,306
Especially Felix.

183
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:43,100
Especially that bastard.

184
00:10:45,394 --> 00:10:47,104
I will give justice to Father,

185
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:49,273
to Sir Mustapha,

186
00:10:50,358 --> 00:10:52,777
and all of Carillo's victims.

187
00:10:53,694 --> 00:10:54,904
[in Arabic] God has willed it.

188
00:10:59,575 --> 00:11:05,373
We're here on Alejandro Avenue,
where a public protest is ongoing.

189
00:11:05,456 --> 00:11:07,792
This is just one of the many protests

190
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:10,878
happening across different parts
of the country.

191
00:11:10,961 --> 00:11:12,296
According to the people,

192
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:16,092
they have fully lost their trust
in the government

193
00:11:16,175 --> 00:11:18,302
and in public officials,

194
00:11:18,386 --> 00:11:20,471
especially now that they found out

195
00:11:20,554 --> 00:11:24,141
that General Carillo,
who they thought was a decent man,

196
00:11:24,225 --> 00:11:27,895
was actually the mastermind behind
the chaos across the country.

197
00:11:27,978 --> 00:11:29,230
Sir, what do you have to say?

198
00:11:29,313 --> 00:11:32,316
Nothing! This government
can't really do anything!

199
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,526
You should resign!

200
00:11:34,568 --> 00:11:37,154
The people in power are useless!
They're just thieves!

201
00:11:37,238 --> 00:11:38,948
We can't expect anything from you!

202
00:11:39,824 --> 00:11:42,326
She's right. We were
all counting on Carillo.

203
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:43,869
But he's also useless!

204
00:11:43,953 --> 00:11:46,247
- [chanting] Quit! Quit!
- Mendoza, resign now!

205
00:11:46,330 --> 00:11:48,249
You're weak! We need someone strong!

206
00:11:48,332 --> 00:11:50,418
- Someone with an iron fist!
- That's right!

207
00:11:50,501 --> 00:11:54,088
[chanting] Iron fist! Iron fist!

208
00:11:54,171 --> 00:11:56,006
[foreboding music playing]

209
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:58,217
The protests

210
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:00,386
are no longer limited
to Metro Manila and Luzon.

211
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:03,973
There are now protests
across the Visayas and Mindanao.

212
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:05,933
In fact,

213
00:12:06,016 --> 00:12:08,060
my police officers
can't come home anymore.

214
00:12:08,936 --> 00:12:09,979
[in English] I understand.

215
00:12:10,688 --> 00:12:14,066
We'll also discuss that
at the emergency meeting tomorrow.

216
00:12:15,401 --> 00:12:16,944
General Villanueva,

217
00:12:17,027 --> 00:12:20,364
everyone who'll come tomorrow
is in the succession of power.

218
00:12:20,448 --> 00:12:23,701
They can all take over as president

219
00:12:23,784 --> 00:12:25,536
in case something happens to me.

220
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:30,124
So make sure that
our meeting will be secure.

221
00:12:30,207 --> 00:12:31,459
If not,

222
00:12:32,126 --> 00:12:34,545
we'll have a constitutional crisis,

223
00:12:34,628 --> 00:12:36,338
and the whole country will be in chaos.

224
00:12:36,422 --> 00:12:38,132
[in English] You have my word,
Madam President.

225
00:12:38,215 --> 00:12:39,383
[in English] Good.

226
00:12:43,053 --> 00:12:45,055
I don't think I've ever
seen you here before.

227
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:47,141
[in English] Yes, Madam President.

228
00:12:47,725 --> 00:12:50,019
SPO4 Felix Domingo.

229
00:12:50,102 --> 00:12:52,646
I was formerly
in Task Force Alpha, but now

230
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:57,109
I'm a part
of your Presidential Security Group.

231
00:12:58,027 --> 00:12:59,236
Oh.

232
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:01,405
[in English] TFA, one of the elites.

233
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:05,951
If so, then you can easily protect me.

234
00:13:07,328 --> 00:13:08,662
[in English] With my life, madam.

235
00:13:08,746 --> 00:13:11,832
[dramatic sting]

236
00:13:25,137 --> 00:13:28,474
If you'll notice, out of 82 provinces,

237
00:13:29,099 --> 00:13:30,518
we've secured 37.

238
00:13:30,601 --> 00:13:31,852
That's not even half.

239
00:13:32,436 --> 00:13:34,063
You're right.

240
00:13:34,146 --> 00:13:36,148
But every province we've secured

241
00:13:36,732 --> 00:13:39,652
is a first-class province or region.

242
00:13:39,735 --> 00:13:44,323
And every one of them has a military camp

243
00:13:44,406 --> 00:13:46,700
and an NLEA regional office.

244
00:13:47,701 --> 00:13:51,247
The 93rd Infantry Battalion in Region IV…

245
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:53,040
I went to the academy
with their commander.

246
00:13:54,166 --> 00:13:55,501
Leave them to me.

247
00:13:55,584 --> 00:13:56,752
Once Martial Law is declared…

248
00:13:57,253 --> 00:13:59,421
And when the march is declared,

249
00:14:00,130 --> 00:14:02,716
they'll back the movement.

250
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,593
And then,

251
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:08,097
nothing will stand
in General Carillo's way.

252
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:11,517
By tomorrow, we'll have a new republic.

253
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,477
To the new republic!

254
00:14:13,561 --> 00:14:15,437
- To the new republic!
- To the new republic!

255
00:14:15,521 --> 00:14:19,275
[dark music playing]

256
00:14:23,946 --> 00:14:28,409
Malacañang is now preparing
for a special emergency meeting

257
00:14:28,492 --> 00:14:31,370
called by President Natalia Mendoza.

258
00:14:31,453 --> 00:14:34,623
<i>This comes in response</i>
<i>to the public's demand</i>

259
00:14:34,707 --> 00:14:38,544
<i>for stronger and more</i>
<i>effective national security.</i>

260
00:14:39,128 --> 00:14:42,464
<i>Officials in the presidential</i>
<i>line of succession</i>

261
00:14:42,548 --> 00:14:44,383
<i>are expected to attend,</i>

262
00:14:44,466 --> 00:14:47,052
<i>including Vice President Kevin Flores,</i>

263
00:14:47,136 --> 00:14:49,638
<i>Senate President Joshua Manzon,</i>

264
00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:53,309
<i>Speaker of the House of Representatives</i>
<i>Samantha Santos,</i>

265
00:14:53,392 --> 00:14:56,604
<i>and Chief Justice Leona Caluag.</i>

266
00:14:58,606 --> 00:15:01,567
As long as Carillo's accomplices
are still out there,

267
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:03,402
our mission isn't over.

268
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:07,573
That's why we have
to find them immediately.

269
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:11,327
I'm calling in Task Force Alpha.

270
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:16,665
We urgently need to address
the country's security concerns.

271
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:19,710
[Villanueva] <i>That's why we've invited</i>
<i>the highest-ranking government officials,</i>

272
00:15:19,793 --> 00:15:23,464
<i>from the Vice President</i>
<i>to the Senate President,</i>

273
00:15:23,547 --> 00:15:26,675
<i>the Speaker of the House,</i>
<i>and even the Chief Justice.</i>

274
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:28,844
[reporter] <i>And they've all</i>
<i>confirmed they're coming?</i>

275
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:30,971
[Villanueva, in English] <i>Yes.</i>

276
00:15:31,055 --> 00:15:33,390
[in English] <i>Each and every one of them.</i>

277
00:15:34,016 --> 00:15:35,351
They're all coming.

278
00:15:35,434 --> 00:15:37,728
[ominous music playing]

279
00:15:37,811 --> 00:15:39,939
The very people who are next in line

280
00:15:40,022 --> 00:15:43,525
if the President dies or is assassinated.

281
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:46,737
If that place is attacked
and they all die,

282
00:15:47,696 --> 00:15:49,698
there'll be no one left
to lead the Philippines.

283
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:52,368
And taking over the government
will be easy.

284
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:00,376
MALACAÑANG IS PREPARING
AN URGENT MEETING FOR NATIONAL SECURITY.

285
00:16:00,459 --> 00:16:01,669
[suspenseful music playing]

286
00:16:01,752 --> 00:16:03,003
Is that Felix?

287
00:16:04,922 --> 00:16:06,298
That conference.

288
00:16:07,091 --> 00:16:10,177
That's their target.
That's where General Carillo will strike.

289
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:14,765
How did that bastard get assigned
to the President's Security Group?

290
00:16:14,848 --> 00:16:16,684
General Villanueva.

291
00:16:16,767 --> 00:16:17,893
No one else.

292
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:20,312
He's the only one who could've
recommended Domingo

293
00:16:20,396 --> 00:16:21,689
to join the President's security detail.

294
00:16:22,272 --> 00:16:24,149
He's working with General Carillo.

295
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:25,734
General Carillo's been able
to keep operating

296
00:16:25,818 --> 00:16:27,111
because of him!

297
00:16:27,611 --> 00:16:30,197
[music intensifies]

298
00:16:48,882 --> 00:16:53,762
[ominous music continues]

299
00:16:55,723 --> 00:16:57,266
[music stops]

300
00:16:57,349 --> 00:16:59,435
What's Marcus and Jalil up to now?

301
00:16:59,518 --> 00:17:02,104
They're always sabotaging our plans.

302
00:17:02,688 --> 00:17:04,440
Relax. Don't worry.

303
00:17:05,607 --> 00:17:07,276
If those two interfere again,

304
00:17:07,985 --> 00:17:10,362
General Carillo has our insurance.

305
00:17:10,446 --> 00:17:14,366
[ominous music playing]

306
00:17:30,841 --> 00:17:31,717
[Usman] Auntie.

307
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:33,719
- Thank you so much, Usman.
- You're welcome.

308
00:17:35,179 --> 00:17:36,722
Come on. Let's grab a snack inside.

309
00:17:37,598 --> 00:17:38,474
- [Jamilah] Okay.
- Sure.

310
00:17:39,975 --> 00:17:41,435
[tires screeching]

311
00:17:42,311 --> 00:17:43,270
- Hey!
- You're coming with us!

312
00:17:43,353 --> 00:17:45,355
- Wait, wait!
- Help!

313
00:17:45,439 --> 00:17:46,815
Help!

314
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:48,567
[tense music playing]

315
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:50,069
[man grunts]

316
00:17:50,152 --> 00:17:51,403
[Jamilah grunts]

317
00:17:53,864 --> 00:17:56,033
[Jamilah grunting]

318
00:17:56,617 --> 00:17:57,868
[Teresa gasps]

319
00:17:57,951 --> 00:17:59,161
[Jamilah grunts]

320
00:17:59,244 --> 00:18:00,204
Stop it!

321
00:18:01,872 --> 00:18:03,123
Doctor Teresa!

322
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:06,210
[Usman grunts]

323
00:18:06,293 --> 00:18:08,170
[man 1] Get them in the van! Move! Hurry!

324
00:18:08,754 --> 00:18:10,547
- What do you want with us?
- [Jamilah] Doctor Teresa!

325
00:18:10,631 --> 00:18:12,466
- [Teresa] Let us go!
- [man 2] Stop fighting!

326
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:26,355
[tires screeching]

327
00:18:37,699 --> 00:18:39,118
What do you want with Doctor Teresa?

328
00:18:44,623 --> 00:18:47,584
Wait. I'm not your enemy.

329
00:18:51,046 --> 00:18:52,172
I'm on your side.

330
00:19:07,896 --> 00:19:09,439
[woman 1] What's taking so long?

331
00:19:09,523 --> 00:19:11,275
[woman 2] We've been waiting for hours.

332
00:19:12,067 --> 00:19:14,403
- [woman 1] Where is it?
- [woman 2] Right there.

333
00:19:14,486 --> 00:19:17,281
[indistinct dialogue]

334
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:20,242
Alright. Go find the President.

335
00:19:20,325 --> 00:19:21,243
[man 1] What time
is the press conference starting?

336
00:19:21,326 --> 00:19:22,452
[Maye Mae, in English] Go.

337
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:25,539
[man 2] Get the camera.
It's about to start.

338
00:19:25,622 --> 00:19:27,374
[woman 1] Go. Call them!

339
00:19:27,457 --> 00:19:29,543
- [man 1] Did they even give a time?
- [woman] I don't know.

340
00:19:29,626 --> 00:19:33,005
[man 2] Not answering.

341
00:19:33,088 --> 00:19:37,467
[ominous music continues]

342
00:19:43,557 --> 00:19:45,601
- [indistinct chattering]
- [door thuds]

343
00:19:45,684 --> 00:19:47,144
- [man 1] Hey, why'd they close it?
- [man 2] Why'd they lock it?

344
00:19:51,064 --> 00:19:52,774
- [man 3] Sir, please open the door!
- [woman] What now?

345
00:19:52,858 --> 00:19:54,109
[security] Stay where you are.
Nobody leaves.

346
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:55,444
Sir, please let us out!

347
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:58,030
- There's no signal.
- What do you mean?

348
00:19:58,113 --> 00:19:59,615
- Our signals are being jammed?
- Huh?

349
00:19:59,698 --> 00:20:01,200
[man 4] I think we're being jammed.

350
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:05,370
[ominous music continues]

351
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:06,830
- Let us out!
- [banging on door]

352
00:20:07,456 --> 00:20:08,665
[woman] Please!

353
00:20:08,749 --> 00:20:10,083
[security] Nobody's leaving!
Stay where you are!

354
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:11,376
- [knocks on door]
- [woman] What?

355
00:20:11,460 --> 00:20:12,961
[man] Let us out!

356
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:18,508
[music intensifies]

357
00:20:38,403 --> 00:20:40,405
- [rapid gunfire]
- [people screaming]

358
00:20:41,823 --> 00:20:43,367
- Get down!
- [screaming continues]

359
00:20:44,159 --> 00:20:46,119
[sinister music playing]

360
00:20:46,203 --> 00:20:47,037
‪[gunshots blasting]

361
00:20:50,958 --> 00:20:53,710
[people screaming]

362
00:20:53,794 --> 00:20:55,212
Bud, did you hear the gunshots?

363
00:20:55,295 --> 00:20:56,630
Yes, I think they came from over there!

364
00:20:56,713 --> 00:20:58,257
- Come on!
- Let's go!

365
00:20:58,340 --> 00:20:59,841
- [gunshots]
- [bodies thud]

366
00:21:00,634 --> 00:21:02,010
[gasping]

367
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:04,930
[gunshots blasting]

368
00:21:06,890 --> 00:21:08,225
- [Felix] Come with me!
- [Natalia] Wait--

369
00:21:09,893 --> 00:21:12,104
- The president is under attack!
- Come on!

370
00:21:12,187 --> 00:21:13,897
Who are you working for?

371
00:21:13,981 --> 00:21:16,066
- Tell me!
- Shut up!

372
00:21:16,149 --> 00:21:17,776
- [Felix] I will kill you.
- [Natalia gasps]

373
00:21:19,236 --> 00:21:20,487
[Felix] Move!

374
00:21:20,570 --> 00:21:23,573
- [tense music playing]
- [gasping]

375
00:21:23,657 --> 00:21:26,994
- What happened in there?
- Bud, they need backup inside!

376
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:28,036
Come on!

377
00:21:29,371 --> 00:21:30,789
[guns cock, shots blasting]

378
00:21:30,872 --> 00:21:33,750
[people crying, screaming]

379
00:21:36,169 --> 00:21:37,671
[gunshots blasting]

380
00:21:37,754 --> 00:21:40,257
[tense music continues]

381
00:21:53,395 --> 00:21:57,524
[music turns grim]

382
00:22:04,364 --> 00:22:05,699
The president's not here.

383
00:22:06,950 --> 00:22:08,452
We need to find her.

384
00:22:08,535 --> 00:22:11,955
[tense music playing]

385
00:22:12,039 --> 00:22:13,457
EMBLEM OF THE PRESIDENT OF THE PHILIPPINES

386
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:35,604
[dark music playing]

387
00:22:49,868 --> 00:22:53,997
[dark music continues]

388
00:23:06,635 --> 00:23:07,969
Let me go!

389
00:23:09,387 --> 00:23:11,098
Where are you taking me?

390
00:23:11,598 --> 00:23:13,058
What are you-- Oh, security.

391
00:23:13,141 --> 00:23:14,476
Security, help!

392
00:23:14,559 --> 00:23:16,269
Help me! [gasps]

393
00:23:18,146 --> 00:23:19,564
[Natalia] Traitors!

394
00:23:20,273 --> 00:23:21,775
What are you going to do with me?

395
00:23:35,914 --> 00:23:37,999
- [Manuel] Ah…
- [Natalia grunts]

396
00:23:38,083 --> 00:23:39,543
[chuckles]

397
00:23:39,626 --> 00:23:42,087
[in English] Finally! Good job, Felix!

398
00:23:43,171 --> 00:23:47,551
Alright. [clicks tongue]
Go get my leverage.

399
00:23:47,634 --> 00:23:48,468
‪[dramatic sting]

400
00:23:49,803 --> 00:23:51,012
[in English] Yes, sir.

401
00:23:51,304 --> 00:23:52,139
‪[thud]

402
00:23:54,516 --> 00:23:56,184
[Manuel sighs loudly, chuckles]

403
00:23:56,268 --> 00:23:57,894
Madam President,

404
00:23:57,978 --> 00:24:00,897
your chair is quite comfortable.

405
00:24:00,981 --> 00:24:03,608
[in English] I think
I'm going to like it here.

406
00:24:04,609 --> 00:24:06,319
[in English] Not on my watch.

407
00:24:07,821 --> 00:24:11,700
[tense music playing]

408
00:24:14,244 --> 00:24:16,037
[grunting]

409
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:17,664
- [Natalia grunts]
- [Solares grunts]

410
00:24:17,747 --> 00:24:21,293
Mustapha taught me how to defend myself!

411
00:24:21,376 --> 00:24:22,711
[gun cocks]

412
00:24:23,461 --> 00:24:24,337
Go ahead.

413
00:24:25,297 --> 00:24:28,675
If you want to keep
fighting until you die,

414
00:24:28,758 --> 00:24:31,595
go ahead. Make my day!

415
00:24:32,596 --> 00:24:36,391
[scoffs] But do not forget.

416
00:24:37,684 --> 00:24:42,147
The vice president and everyone else

417
00:24:42,230 --> 00:24:44,316
in the line of succession are gone.

418
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:49,654
This will all be mine the moment you die.

419
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:51,281
Damn you, Manuel.

420
00:24:54,743 --> 00:24:57,037
[line beeping]

421
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:58,496
Did you get a signal?

422
00:24:59,164 --> 00:25:01,041
- Not yet.
- [beeping continues]

423
00:25:02,042 --> 00:25:05,587
- Let me go!
- [in English] Madam President.

424
00:25:06,379 --> 00:25:10,425
The Philippines is in turmoil.

425
00:25:10,508 --> 00:25:12,510
Everywhere you look,

426
00:25:13,345 --> 00:25:14,971
if there isn't a crime happening,

427
00:25:15,639 --> 00:25:17,224
there's a protest.

428
00:25:17,307 --> 00:25:19,684
People are angry.

429
00:25:21,436 --> 00:25:26,608
You have to declare Martial Law.

430
00:25:27,192 --> 00:25:31,821
And you have to convince the public

431
00:25:31,905 --> 00:25:34,407
that this is what the country needs!

432
00:25:34,491 --> 00:25:38,203
I know a psychiatrist. Get checked out!

433
00:25:38,828 --> 00:25:41,957
[in English] You're not a savior,
you're a psychopath!

434
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:47,462
[Manuel scoffs]
We need change, Madam President,

435
00:25:47,545 --> 00:25:52,217
and it won't be possible

436
00:25:52,300 --> 00:25:57,847
with leaders like you
because you are weak.

437
00:25:59,307 --> 00:26:02,477
[in English] We need to burn
the whole system down.

438
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:06,356
[in English] The system that allows

439
00:26:06,439 --> 00:26:10,610
weaklings like yourself to rule!

440
00:26:13,488 --> 00:26:17,033
And from the ashes,

441
00:26:17,617 --> 00:26:23,707
peace and progress will be reborn

442
00:26:24,708 --> 00:26:27,919
for The New Republic.

443
00:26:29,296 --> 00:26:30,588
[in English] No.

444
00:26:31,548 --> 00:26:35,010
I'm not going to give you what you want!

445
00:26:35,093 --> 00:26:36,636
[Manuel] But, Madam President…

446
00:26:37,512 --> 00:26:42,309
your vice president is dead!

447
00:26:42,392 --> 00:26:46,980
And everyone else
in the line of succession!

448
00:26:47,063 --> 00:26:52,861
My people are ready
to launch a coup d'état.

449
00:26:53,445 --> 00:26:57,657
I will get what I want

450
00:26:58,283 --> 00:27:00,952
once you're gone.

451
00:27:02,412 --> 00:27:05,248
That is, if…

452
00:27:05,832 --> 00:27:11,796
you want the bloodshed to continue.

453
00:27:12,547 --> 00:27:16,426
[in English] You can kill me,
but you will never succeed.

454
00:27:17,093 --> 00:27:19,346
Don't underestimate the Filipinos.

455
00:27:20,263 --> 00:27:21,765
Because even if I'm gone,

456
00:27:21,848 --> 00:27:25,643
there are people who'll take
my place to fight against you.

457
00:27:25,727 --> 00:27:30,065
Because they will never be fooled
by a psychopath like you!

458
00:27:30,148 --> 00:27:31,649
- [grunts]
- [Natalia yelps]

459
00:27:32,233 --> 00:27:33,777
[Natalia gasps]

460
00:27:33,860 --> 00:27:35,028
[Manuel] No!

461
00:27:36,112 --> 00:27:37,947
You're wrong!

462
00:27:38,031 --> 00:27:40,909
You're wrong! This is mine!

463
00:27:41,534 --> 00:27:45,455
Do you understand? This throne is mine!

464
00:27:46,664 --> 00:27:49,584
This throne is mine!

465
00:27:49,667 --> 00:27:52,504
[laughs maniacally]

466
00:27:52,587 --> 00:27:54,464
It's mine!

467
00:27:54,547 --> 00:27:56,758
It's mine!

468
00:27:59,677 --> 00:28:03,681
[tense music playing]

469
00:28:06,726 --> 00:28:08,269
- It's Axl Rosales!
- No, wait!

470
00:28:08,353 --> 00:28:10,021
- Wait!
- Calm down!

471
00:28:10,730 --> 00:28:11,856
He's on our side.

472
00:28:11,940 --> 00:28:13,900
- What?
- [Azuelo] Sabdani.

473
00:28:13,983 --> 00:28:15,193
What's going on?

474
00:28:15,276 --> 00:28:19,614
Sir, Jamilah, Jalil's sister,
and Dr. Reyes

475
00:28:19,697 --> 00:28:21,116
was kidnapped by armed men.

476
00:28:21,199 --> 00:28:22,617
Dr. Reyes?

477
00:28:22,700 --> 00:28:24,119
Yes, sir.

478
00:28:24,202 --> 00:28:26,871
She is the mother of Jalil and Marcus.

479
00:28:28,123 --> 00:28:30,625
Jalil is Marcus Reyes' missing brother.

480
00:28:30,708 --> 00:28:31,626
He's Gabriel.

481
00:28:31,709 --> 00:28:33,169
Who kidnapped them?

482
00:28:33,253 --> 00:28:34,379
Felix Domingo.

483
00:28:35,547 --> 00:28:37,924
I recognized one of the armed men.

484
00:28:38,007 --> 00:28:40,719
He's one of Felix Domingo's men.

485
00:28:41,302 --> 00:28:43,596
Felix Domingo, you bastard!

486
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:46,015
Why would Sir Felix do that?

487
00:28:47,308 --> 00:28:49,686
Sir, they're right.

488
00:28:50,311 --> 00:28:52,731
When I broke into
General Villanueva's office,

489
00:28:52,814 --> 00:28:56,401
I found out that he recommended Domingo
to become part of the PSG.

490
00:28:58,653 --> 00:29:01,239
That's right, sir. I saw it on the news.

491
00:29:01,322 --> 00:29:04,617
Sir Felix is now part
of the President's security detail.

492
00:29:05,994 --> 00:29:08,037
Sir, they're attacking Malacañang now.

493
00:29:08,747 --> 00:29:10,623
[Usman] What? Sir.

494
00:29:10,707 --> 00:29:12,459
[in English] Move! Move out!

495
00:29:16,087 --> 00:29:18,173
You won't succeed!

496
00:29:19,132 --> 00:29:20,633
Even if you kill me,

497
00:29:20,717 --> 00:29:23,386
someone will stop your evil plans!

498
00:29:26,097 --> 00:29:27,849
[Villanueva on radio]
<i>Lawin to Alpha. Come in. Over.</i>

499
00:29:30,727 --> 00:29:32,437
- [in English] Go, Villanueva.
- [radio static]

500
00:29:32,520 --> 00:29:35,148
Marcus Reyes and Jalil Abubakar are here.

501
00:29:35,732 --> 00:29:37,108
- [Villanueva] <i>They're inside.</i>
- [radio static]

502
00:29:37,192 --> 00:29:39,903
[suspenseful music playing]

503
00:29:40,779 --> 00:29:41,821
[in English] See?

504
00:29:42,906 --> 00:29:44,699
My allies have arrived.

505
00:29:45,283 --> 00:29:48,745
The people who are helping me
stop your evil plans.

506
00:29:49,329 --> 00:29:51,039
[in English] And I'm sure
they're not alone.

507
00:29:51,623 --> 00:29:55,293
The entire Philippines is behind them
to fight against you!

508
00:29:59,923 --> 00:30:01,883
[in English] Kill them, Villanueva.

509
00:30:02,550 --> 00:30:08,097
Make sure none of them survives.

510
00:30:08,723 --> 00:30:10,308
- [Villanueva, in English] <i>Roger, sir.</i>
- [radio static]

511
00:30:10,391 --> 00:30:11,309
[walkie-talkie thuds]

512
00:30:14,354 --> 00:30:17,273
[music intensifies]

513
00:30:21,945 --> 00:30:22,904
[grunting]

514
00:30:26,074 --> 00:30:27,158
This way.

515
00:30:30,036 --> 00:30:31,287
Hey! Stop!

516
00:30:31,371 --> 00:30:33,915
[gunshots blasting]

517
00:30:40,338 --> 00:30:41,339
Let's use this to block the door.

518
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:45,468
[grunts]

519
00:30:48,137 --> 00:30:50,014
This is Sir Mustapha’s office.

520
00:30:50,598 --> 00:30:51,808
He had an armory at his house.

521
00:30:51,891 --> 00:30:52,934
He probably has one here too.

522
00:30:53,017 --> 00:30:54,602
Let's look for the lock.

523
00:30:54,686 --> 00:30:57,897
- [door rattling]
- [breathing heavily]

524
00:30:57,981 --> 00:30:59,023
Open the door!

525
00:30:59,732 --> 00:31:01,442
You have nowhere left to go!

526
00:31:04,904 --> 00:31:06,030
[grunts]

527
00:31:06,739 --> 00:31:08,116
- Here!
- Okay!

528
00:31:11,828 --> 00:31:13,621
[man 1] Come out!

529
00:31:15,874 --> 00:31:17,959
You have nowhere left to go!

530
00:31:18,585 --> 00:31:21,004
[man 2] Just surrender! You can't escape!

531
00:31:24,841 --> 00:31:26,843
[gunshots blasting]

532
00:31:40,815 --> 00:31:42,442
[police siren honking, tires screeching]

533
00:31:43,318 --> 00:31:44,986
- [guard 1] Someone's coming!
- [guard 2] Who is it?

534
00:31:45,069 --> 00:31:48,197
- [tires screech]
- [siren blares]

535
00:31:48,781 --> 00:31:52,452
I am Director Azuelo
of the Special Investigations Division.

536
00:31:52,535 --> 00:31:54,495
I'm with Task Force Alpha.

537
00:31:54,579 --> 00:31:56,956
We need to talk to the President.

538
00:31:57,040 --> 00:31:58,917
You can't talk to her. She's busy.

539
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,376
She's currently in a meeting.

540
00:32:02,879 --> 00:32:04,047
[guard 1] Leave!

541
00:32:07,759 --> 00:32:08,635
[Azuelo, in English] Fire at will!

542
00:32:08,718 --> 00:32:10,553
- [both yell]
- [rapid gunfire]

543
00:32:15,683 --> 00:32:20,229
[suspenseful music playing]

544
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:25,401
[Azuelo, in English] Move! Move!

545
00:32:25,485 --> 00:32:27,236
[metal gate creaks]

546
00:32:32,533 --> 00:32:33,785
Do you hear those gunshots?

547
00:32:35,453 --> 00:32:36,371
[Solares] Those are your allies.

548
00:32:36,996 --> 00:32:39,582
The people you expect to protect you
are being killed.

549
00:32:39,666 --> 00:32:40,875
[in English] You wish.

550
00:32:40,959 --> 00:32:42,627
I know they're all good fighters.

551
00:32:42,710 --> 00:32:44,545
That's why Ahmad trusted them.

552
00:32:44,629 --> 00:32:46,714
[cackles]

553
00:32:46,798 --> 00:32:48,508
Natalia! Natalia!

554
00:32:48,591 --> 00:32:52,553
I pity your naivety!

555
00:32:52,637 --> 00:32:55,723
If you really love this country,

556
00:32:55,807 --> 00:32:58,226
you will give me what I want!

557
00:32:58,309 --> 00:33:01,980
Manuel, if you really love the country,

558
00:33:02,063 --> 00:33:05,984
can you please just drop dead? Now!

559
00:33:06,567 --> 00:33:08,695
[in English] We move on to Plan B.

560
00:33:08,778 --> 00:33:09,988
[in English] Yes, General.

561
00:33:10,071 --> 00:33:11,364
[Manuel snaps fingers]

562
00:33:15,118 --> 00:33:16,244
What is this?

563
00:33:16,327 --> 00:33:18,037
In 15 minutes,

564
00:33:18,621 --> 00:33:22,166
the Philippines will lose its president.

565
00:33:22,750 --> 00:33:25,128
[dark music plays]

566
00:33:27,463 --> 00:33:29,799
[in English] You really are a psychopath.

567
00:33:29,882 --> 00:33:32,844
And the news will say

568
00:33:33,928 --> 00:33:37,098
that you were killed by Marcus Reyes

569
00:33:37,181 --> 00:33:40,059
and Jalil Abubakar

570
00:33:40,143 --> 00:33:42,770
to seize power.

571
00:33:43,563 --> 00:33:48,109
While I will declare a military junta

572
00:33:48,192 --> 00:33:52,780
to save the Republic!

573
00:33:53,406 --> 00:33:54,532
And

574
00:33:55,241 --> 00:34:00,621
it will all happen in 15 minutes.

575
00:34:00,705 --> 00:34:04,542
Which means I have 15 minutes

576
00:34:04,625 --> 00:34:06,377
to beat you.

577
00:34:06,878 --> 00:34:09,130
[in English] Be my guest, Natalia.

578
00:34:09,213 --> 00:34:13,384
It never hurts to try.

579
00:34:13,468 --> 00:34:16,804
- [bomb activates, ticking]
- [in English] In 15 minutes…

580
00:34:17,513 --> 00:34:20,141
- [in English] Tick-tock-tick-tock…
- [huffs]

581
00:34:20,224 --> 00:34:21,601
[chuckles]

582
00:34:22,268 --> 00:34:23,853
[Manuel sighs deeply] In 15 minutes,

583
00:34:23,936 --> 00:34:27,273
the Philippines will be mine!

584
00:34:27,356 --> 00:34:31,069
[tense music playing]

585
00:34:33,780 --> 00:34:35,990
[music intensifies]

586
00:34:36,074 --> 00:34:37,075
[music fades]

587
00:34:37,158 --> 00:34:39,118
[Teresa] Let us go!

588
00:34:39,202 --> 00:34:43,664
- [stirring music playing]
- [heavy breathing]

589
00:34:43,748 --> 00:34:48,002
[Teresa, Jamilah breathing heavily]

590
00:34:48,086 --> 00:34:49,295
[Felix] Teresa.

591
00:34:51,089 --> 00:34:52,173
[bullet clinks]

592
00:34:52,256 --> 00:34:54,092
- Felix…
- Jamilah.

593
00:34:55,259 --> 00:34:56,552
Felix…

594
00:34:57,136 --> 00:34:58,471
- [Teresa] Felix…
- How are you?

595
00:35:02,308 --> 00:35:03,851
What does this all mean?

596
00:35:03,935 --> 00:35:05,520
Felix, what is this?

597
00:35:08,439 --> 00:35:09,941
Jalil is your brother.

598
00:35:10,566 --> 00:35:13,528
[stirring music continues]

599
00:35:13,611 --> 00:35:15,196
And Marcus is your son.

600
00:35:16,656 --> 00:35:20,576
[Felix chuckles]
I'll invite them over to see you guys.

601
00:35:21,619 --> 00:35:22,745
I'll have them watch me kill you.

602
00:35:22,829 --> 00:35:24,914
[suspenseful stinging]

603
00:35:27,041 --> 00:35:28,292
Because they…

604
00:35:28,960 --> 00:35:30,419
are my…

605
00:35:31,212 --> 00:35:33,047
worst enemies.

606
00:35:33,131 --> 00:35:34,340
[breath quivers]

607
00:35:36,008 --> 00:35:41,597
[stirring music continues]

608
00:35:41,681 --> 00:35:43,766
[gunfire blasting]

609
00:35:44,851 --> 00:35:46,310
[in English] Reload!

610
00:35:46,394 --> 00:35:47,687
[tense music playing]

611
00:35:59,323 --> 00:36:00,408
[in English] Reload!

612
00:36:03,995 --> 00:36:05,913
[rapid gunfire]

613
00:36:11,460 --> 00:36:12,670
[Felix] <i>Shall we play a game?</i>

614
00:36:12,753 --> 00:36:14,213
<i>Do you know how to hold a gun?</i>

615
00:36:14,297 --> 00:36:16,632
Do you have any idea what we have to do

616
00:36:16,716 --> 00:36:19,552
to fix this goddamn government?

617
00:36:19,635 --> 00:36:21,804
This is what the country needs.

618
00:36:21,888 --> 00:36:24,056
We don't need an iron fist.
We need justice!

619
00:36:24,140 --> 00:36:25,892
You can't keep us apart anymore.

620
00:36:27,768 --> 00:36:29,061
[rapid gunfire]

621
00:36:29,145 --> 00:36:30,438
- [officer] <i>Let's force it.</i>
- [beeping]

622
00:36:30,521 --> 00:36:31,355
<i>It's gonna blow up.</i>

623
00:36:31,439 --> 00:36:32,648
[grunting]

624
00:36:33,691 --> 00:36:35,568
- [gunshots blasting]
- [Felix] <i>Marcus! Jalil!</i>

625
00:36:36,152 --> 00:36:38,946
<i>I have a surprise for you!</i>
